      I like the idea of accountability. I dislike the idea of accountability being in the form of a "report." At best, states will shove the project onto the desk of someone who is already overworked and underpaid. At worst a report will be twisted glorification of the efforts of state government regardless of politics, corruption or other inherent problems.<br/><br/>There must be a better way to achieve accountability. Perhaps citizens of each state should be able to vote on-line in regards to how they perceive their governments level of transparency. I'd be interested in hearing about alternatives to "reports".<br/><br/>

                  
    </td>
  </tr>


