      Accountability is a critical aspect of these efforts, and can be achieved through a variety of mechanisms. Written reports are a tool familiar to agency managers, and can provide in-depth understanding of the agency's performance on participation, collaboration and transparency. Other types of performance measurement and scorecard systems should also be used, and, as said above, "be modified to include transparency, participation and collaboration criteria and metrics."<br/><br/>The other important aspect of this recommendation is a commitment by government leaders, in word and action, to the OGD. Leadership can help set a new tone and ensure expectations are met about reaching these goals of open government.

                  
    </td>
  </tr>


